    obtain вҹЁi, hiвҹ© := h2
    ```
    This gives `i : в„•` and `hi : ПҶ вҲҲ construction T hT i`.

4.  Now we have `i` such that `ПҶ вҲҲ construction T hT i`. We also have `h1 : L вҠў ПҶ вҶ’ ПҲ`. The property `T.imp_closed` (which is `T`'s `imp_closed` field) states that `T` is closed under implications: `вҲҖ {ПҶ ПҲ}, L вҠў ПҶ вҶ’ ПҲ вҶ’ ПҶ вҲҲ T вҶ’ ПҲ вҲҲ T`. We can use these to derive `ПҲ вҲҲ construction T hT i`.
